# RuntimeControl — Phase 2 of the runtime action protocol.
#
# Sent: backend / CLI → mission_control_node (after SetMission + EBS release).
# sim_supervisor_node passively relays feedback to /fsds/control_command.
#
# Opened once Phase 1 (SetMission) reports success=true. Carries the
# control-loop traffic for the duration of the mission: control_node's
# throttle/steering proposals flow back from mission_control_node as
# feedback, and `emergency` / `finished` flags from slam_node terminate
# the action with a defined outcome.
#
# On the real car the same action is exchanged between
# mission_control_node and the physical uDV (microROS endpoint over
# USB CDC). Semantics are identical; only the DDS transport differs.

# ---------------- Goal ----------------
# Empty — opening the action is the request itself. The action stays
# open until terminated by `finished`, `emergency`, or supervisor-side
# cancellation (e.g. operator pressed RES).

---
# ---------------- Result ----------------
# Why the runtime phase ended. One of:
#   "finished"   — slam_node detected mission completion (e.g. lap-min
#                  distance + big-orange detection)
#   "emergency"  — slam_node or another node raised emergency=true
#   "cancelled"  — supervisor cancelled (operator RES, mission switch)
#   "error"      — unexpected failure inside mission_control_node
string outcome

# Human-readable diagnostic; empty unless outcome=="error".
string message

---
# ---------------- Feedback ----------------
# Per-tick control commands as they leave control_node. The supervisor
# publishes these onto /fsds/control_command for the bridge to forward
# into UE5. On the real car the same fields go to the uDV directly.
float32 throttle    # [-1.0, 1.0] — negative = regen
float32 steering    # [-1.0, 1.0] — left positive
bool    emergency   # true → request EBS
bool    finished    # true → mission complete
builtin_interfaces/Time stamp
